!! Q: My plugin doesn't appear in the settings hub. Why?

The hub discovers plugins via the filter `[plugin-type[plugin]prefix[$:/plugins/rimir/]]`. Check that:

* Your plugin is listed in `tiddlywiki.info` under `plugins`
* The plugin title starts with `$:/plugins/rimir/`
* You restarted the server after adding the plugin

Note that core-hook itself is excluded from the sidebar list.

!! Q: Can I use the settings hub without the theme plugin?

The hub layout depends on `rr-settings-*` CSS classes defined in the theme plugin. Without theme, the hub will render but without proper styling (no sidebar layout, no accent borders, no spacing).

!! Q: How does the hub decide which plugin is selected by default?

If no selection state exists in `$:/state/rimir/core-hook/selected`, the hub auto-selects the first plugin alphabetically (via `sort[name]first[]`).

